race.description: 1808 A Rum Bar & Cocktail Lounge Mdn Plate (C1)
race.comment: Tough with every runner rising plenty in trip. OPENSEA (1) keeps the premier hoop (Darmanin) and was tracking well before the latest. Darmanin believed the gelding needed more ground and he gets that today. Hard fit and will get every chance. SKELMORLIE (2) won that race and it was a decent effort after settling back in the field. That indicates she'll manage the step up in trip and can go on with it. TIZSA NICE DROP (3) wasn't far away in the same contest and was beaten a whisker prior. She also has claims. TWICE THE ICE (4) comes out of the same race and dropped out badly. Went close over 1880m on the synthetic prior and that's a better measure of her chances.
